<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,467,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Another species with large, relatively simple cerci and rudimentary surstyli. The phallus has a pair of medial processes in the shape of rounded lobes as in 
<taxonomicName authority="MacGowan" authorityName="MacGowan" box="[1018,1307,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicerca">
<emphasis box="[1018,1167,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">F. longicerca</emphasis>
MacGowan
</taxonomicName>
but in that species the phallus is less angled with smaller medial lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1042,404,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" box="[199,1042,404,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Etymology.</emphasis>
